        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 2:22PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 222 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Chesterfield, or 10 miles northwest of Cheraw, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts 40 to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cheraw, Chesterfield, Cheraw Municipal Airport, Northeastern
Technical College, Ruby, McFarlan, Chesterfield Ruby Middle School,
and Chesterfield Detention Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
